			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I've put together a couple quick-reference charts on what pieces are used to make what bows and arrows with the fletching skill. These charts can be found on my webpage at:<BR>
   http://mosa.unity.ncsu.edu/EQ/<BR>
<BR>
All of the information for these charts came from Aoenla's Fetching Guide, which should be able to tell you everything you need to know about the carft. A link to her site was given earlier in this forum, or can be found on my page above.<BR>
<BR>
Yes, bowyer supplies are a lot harder to find than fletcher supplies. The only one I've found so far is one of the Rangers in the guild hall in Surefall Glade, two zones north of Qeynos. Fletching supplies can be<BR>
found there as well, and in Halas, and also in West Karana. <BR>
<BR>
Haven't made any effort to turn a profit at this craft. I just do it to keep my rogue loaded with a long-range pulling weapon. I try to keep a set of 20 arrow pieces on hand to pass the down-time between battles. Plus, a hickory bow and a couple gross of arrows is a great way to help out newbie.<BR>
<BR>
Althandoor, Barbarian Rogue, Saryrn Server (49 Fletcher)
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
